The four main types of diagnostic testing include:&nbsp;

- Laboratory Tests (e.g., blood tests, urine analysis)&nbsp;
- Radiology Tests (e.g., X-rays, MRI, CT scans)&nbsp;
- Cardiovascular Tests (e.g., ECG, stress tests)&nbsp;
- Genetic &amp; Biopsy Tests (e.g., tissue biopsy, genetic screening)&nbsp;&nbsp;
